description:
The ECUP combines the drive home with cooking dinner by reaching for the RoadKill Helper(TM), with Eclipse 3-D Comics!

Ever so often, someone decides it's time to revive 3-D! Eclipse was guilty of this in a big way during the 1980s. This torrent contains evidence of their delirium. Some of these are actual 3-D versions, some are 2-D B&amp;W editions of the 3-D versions. Not sure where to get the old-fashioned paper glasses anymore but I'm guessing the new 3-D TV glasses will work though. If any of you have them, leave a comment and let us know if they're compatible.

Many hosannas to the creative teams and the scanners! Apprehend it, allot it!



Part the next of this Eclipse upload is 'Ms. Tree'! I hate to cast aspersions but the fact is, Ms. Tree got around, folks. The comic was published by Aardvark-Vanaheim, Renegade Press, Eclipse, Paperjacks Ltd. and even DC - friggin' nympho, man! Many of the issues have either been lost to the mists of time or, less dramatically, just not scanned yet. Our good friend STFmaryville tracked down all the available issues and uploaded them in January of this year. Click the blue text below to get there:
